We studied the fragmentation of species distributions according to methods for calculating habitat fragmentation. We used SDMTools (VanDerWal et al., 2014) to generate patch information from a raster map. To measure species fragmentation we used the coherence index (Jaeger, 2000). The coherence index (CI) is a measure of the probability that two animals placed in different patch areas find each other (Jaeger, 2000). The CI is calculated as: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
